{[%evp 0,31,4,4,50,50,86,52,78,43,55,58,63,26,50,57,45,45,45,21,9,28,28,0,14,6,
79,79,124,41,98,-115,104,184]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 a6 3. g3 b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. d3 e6
6. Nh3 b4 7. Ne2 d5 8. O-O Nf6 (8... dxe4 9. Ng5 Nf6 10. Nf4 {looks dangerous
for Black, but better than the game. The computer holds Black's position
easily, but for a human, the threat Nxe6 looks very dangerous.}) 9. e5 Nfd7 {
another important idea in the 2...a6 variation. Always when we reach the
structure with the pawns on d5 and e5, White has a killing idea f4-f5} 10. f4
Nc6 11. c4 $6 {this wasn't necessary} Nb6 (11... dxc4 {Black missed his chance}
12. dxc4 Qc7 $11) 12. f5 {This move frees all our pieces. Both knights can go
to f4, the f-file is open for the rook, the bishop can go to "g5"} Qd7 13. fxe6
fxe6 14. Ng5 h6 15. Nxe6 $1 Qxe6 16. Nf4 {Black just resigned here. He can't
defend against all White's threats} 1-0

