{[%evp 0,41,20,28,50,51,81,43,60,46,62,50,50,31,18,26,14,7,18,16,100,81,74,52,
30,52,18,-16,141,4,196,207,172,-23,22,103,360,347,348,387,1239,1247,29999,
-30000]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 a6 3. g3 b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. d3 e6 6. Nh3 d6 (6... Nf6 7.
O-O d5 8. e5 Nfd7 9. f4 {This setup is popular, but I think that Black is
already on the verge of losing. White is following with f5 against everything}
g6 {even after this move, the advance f4-f5 is powerful} (9... Nc6 10. f5 {
Ignoring White's threats is a hazardous strategy} Ndxe5 11. fxe6 fxe6 12. Bf4
Bd6 13. Ng5 Bc8 14. Qh5+ g6 15. Qh3 Qe7 16. Rae1 $18) 10. f5 $3 $146 gxf5 11.
Qh5 (11. Bg5 Be7 {Is probably the most accurate move order} 12. Qh5 Nxe5 13. g4
{[%cal Ra1e1]}) 11... Nc6 (11... Nxe5 12. Bg5) 12. Ng5 Qe7 13. Nxd5 exd5 14.
Rxf5 Ndxe5 15. Nxf7 Nxf7 16. Bg5 $18 {Is an illustrative line how quickly
Black can lose here}) 7. O-O Nf6 8. f4 Nc6 9. Be3 (9. f5 {This looks more
logical to me. I didn't find any equality for Black after it} e5 (9... exf5 10.
Nf4 $44 (10. exf5 $14)) 10. Nd5 $16 {[%cal Rh3f2]}) 9... Be7 (9... Qc7 {
was better, to defend the b7-bishop and to take an eye on the e5-break}) 10. e5
$1 dxe5 11. fxe5 Nd7 12. Qg4 g6 $4 (12... O-O {Black shoud have go for the
exchange sacrifice} 13. Bh6 g6 14. Bxf8 Qxf8 15. Bxc6 (15. Nd5 $132) 15... Bxc6
16. Rae1 $14 {White is better, but the fight just start}) 13. Rxf7 $3 {Amazing
long term rook sacrifice} Kxf7 14. Rf1+ Ke8 (14... Kg7 {is not any better
after:} 15. Nf4 $3 Nf8 16. Nh5+ Kg8 17. Qf4 Qe8 18. Nf6+ Bxf6 19. exf6 Qf7 20.
Ne4 $18 {Black is hopeless against the multiple White's threats}) 15. Qxe6
Ndxe5 16. Ne4 {Black's army can't fight against multiple White's threats} Qc7
17. Nf4 Bc8 (17... Kd8 $1 18. Nxc5 Bxc5 19. Qf6+ Kc8 20. Qxh8+ $18) 18. Nf6+ {
White is winning very beautifully with a series of only moves} Kd8 19. Qd5+ $8
Qd6 20. Bxc5 $8 Qxd5 21. Bb6# {A brilliant achievement by the Chinese player
against a very strong player.} 1-0

