1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 c5 4. dxc5 Bxc3+ {This move is recommended in some
sources, but objectively speaking is just bad} 5. bxc3 Nf6 (5... Qa5 {This is
the most popular move, but I can't see any good news for Black after the
maneuver Qd4-b4} 6. Qd4 Nf6 7. Qb4 Qc7 ({the endgame after:} 7... Qxb4 8. cxb4
Nxe4 9. Bb2 $18 {is quite depressing for Black}) 8. Nf3 Nc6 9. Qa4 b6 10. cxb6
Qb7 11. Bd3 $18 axb6 12. Qb3 Na5 13. Qb2 Nxe4 14. c4 Nf6 15. O-O {The bishops
are just too strong} O-O 16. Re1 d6 17. Bh6 Re8 $4 {the last mistake} (17...
Qc7 18. Bxf8 $18 {Black is objectively lost, but can continue the game}) 18.
Qxf6 {1-0 (18) Zhigalko,S (2572)-Iskandarov,M (2535) Lichess.org INT 2021}) 6.
e5 Ne4 7. Bd3 Nxc5 8. Nf3 Nc6 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1 $16 {I can't see any
compensation for the absence of the dark square bishop and the weakened dark
squares} b6 (10... d6 {Black should immediately attack the center. Otherwise
White's attack is unstoppable.}) 11. Bh6 Re8 12. h4 Nxd3 13. cxd3 d6 14. d4 Bg4
15. e6 $1 $18 fxe6 16. Qd3 Qd7 17. Ng5 Bf5 18. Qc4 Na5 19. Qe2 Rac8 20. g4 Rxc3
21. gxf5 exf5 22. d5 Rc4 23. Qb2 Rg4+ 24. Kf1 e5 25. dxe6 Qb7 26. f3 Rxh4 27.
Qf6 Rc8 28. Qf7+ Qxf7 29. exf7+ Kh8 30. Re8+ 1-0

