1. d4 g6 2. e4 Bg7 3. Nc3 c5 4. dxc5 Qa5 {It is well known that this move
leads to big problems for Black} 5. Bd2 Qxc5 6. Nd5 $1 {The key idea, now
White is threatening Bb4} Na6 (6... Nf6 $4 7. Bb4 Qc6 8. Bb5 $18 {it is time
to resign}) 7. Nf3 {[%cal Rb2b4,Rb4b5]} e6 8. Bc3 {good positional idea.
Without the dark-squared bishops, Black can't defend all his weakened squares}
Bxc3+ $2 ({better is} 8... Kf8 $1 9. Bxg7+ Kxg7 10. Nc3 $14) 9. Nxc3 d6 {
what else, otherwise e5 and Ne4 will come} 10. Qd2 Nf6 11. O-O-O O-O 12. Qxd6
Qxf2 13. Qf4 $18 Kg7 14. Bxa6 bxa6 15. Qe5 Qb6 16. Rhf1 Qb8 17. Qd4 Qb6 18. Qe5
Qb8 19. Rd6 Kg8 20. Qd4 Ne8 21. Rd8 Qb6 22. Qxb6 axb6 23. Ne5 Bb7 24. Rxa8 Bxa8
25. Nd7 Nd6 26. Rd1 Nb7 27. Nxf8 Kxf8 28. Rd7 Ke8 29. Rc7 Nd8 30. a4 h5 31. h4
f5 32. exf5 gxf5 33. g3 e5 34. Kd2 f4 35. gxf4 exf4 36. Rc4 f3 37. Ke3 Kd7 38.
Rd4+ Ke8 39. Rb4 Kd7 40. Rxb6 Nf7 41. Rxa6 Bc6 42. Ra7+ Ke6 43. Nb5 Kd5 1-0

