1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Qd2 g6 6. b3 Bh6 7. f4 f5 $1 {
This is the best try for Black, but it is not everybody's taste. I believe
that Black is fine in this line, but the position remains easier for White to
play.} 8. Bb2 Nf6 9. O-O-O (9. Bd3 {is more solid. This move gives White an
option to castle short.} Qa5 10. exf5 (10. O-O-O fxe4) 10... Bxf5 11. Nge2
O-O-O {as you see in this line Black usually castle long} (11... Bxd3 $2 {
This was premature, and Grischuk ended up in a difficult position.} 12. Qxd3
Nb4 13. Qd2 Rc8 14. a3 Nc6 15. O-O-O $16 {1-0 (42) Nakamura,H (2769)-Grischuk,
A (2766) Leuven 2018}) 12. a3 $5 {is an interesting continuation, stopping Nb4}
(12. O-O-O d5 13. Kb1 d4 14. Nb5 Qxd2 15. Rxd2 Bg4 16. Nbxd4 Nxd4 17. Bxd4 Rxd4
18. Nxd4 Bxf4 {Black has enough compensation for the exchange1/2 (45)-1/2 (45)
Le, Q (2713)-Vaibhav,S (2593) Caleta 2020}) 12... Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Qf5 14. Rd1 Bg7
{The position remains complicated, but Black should be fine here. 0-1 (55)
Khismatullin, D (2618)-Sarana,A (2641) Yaroslavl 2019}) 9... Rf8 (9... fxe4 $6
{is a mistake, now White plays h3 followed by g4 and Bg2 and then wins the
pawn back.} 10. h3 $1 (10. g3) 10... O-O 11. Nge2 Be6 12. g4 $16 {[%cal Rf1g2]}
) (9... O-O $2 {Black's king will be very weak on the kingside} 10. Bc4+ Kh8
11. Nf3 $18) 10. exf5 (10. Nge2 {doesn't work very well here. Black can
continue with:} Qa5 11. h3 Nxe4 12. Qe1 Be6 13. Kb1 O-O-O {Black has at least
equal chances 0-1 (34) Swinkels,R (2523) -Warmerdam,M (2608) Rotterdam 2021})
10... Bxf5 {Black's structure is worse, but he has an excellent development}
11. Bb5 (11. g3 $142 Qa5 12. Bd3) 11... Qb6 12. Nge2 (12. Re1 $2 {was recently
played by Shirov, but the engines scream already -2 here} O-O-O 13. Nf3 e5 {
all Black's pieces are active and there is no counterplay for White. Probably
White is already lost. 0-1 (41) Shirov,A (2704)-Santos Latasa,J (2639)
Salamanca 2021}) 12... Ne4 $1 {another great move by Andrei} (12... O-O-O 13.
Bd3 $1 $14 {If White manages to calm the position, then the structural
weaknesses in Black's position will become a serious factor.}) 13. Nxe4 Bxe4
14. Bxc6+ Qxc6 15. Kb1 {it is some dynamic equality and Black didn't have any
problems ending the game in a draw.} e5 16. Rhe1 O-O-O 17. g3 Bf3 18. Qa5 Bxe2
19. Rxe2 exf4 20. Qxa7 f3 21. Re7 Rd7 22. Qa8+ Kc7 23. Qa5+ Kc8 24. Qa8+ Kc7
25. Qa5+ Kc8 26. Qa8+ Kc7 27. Qa5+ 1/2-1/2

