1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. Bxc6 bxc6 5. d3 {As a reminder, White's
strategical plan is to gain space with f4 and eventually push c4 blocking the
advance of Black's doubled c-pawns} d5 6. f4 Nf6 7. Nf3 Be7 (7... dxe4 {
is a mistake as it makes Black's structure even worse} 8. dxe4 (8. Nxe4) 8...
Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 $16 {White is better because of Black's weaknesses on the
queenside} Ba6 10. Be3 Rd8+ 11. Kc1 (11. Ke1 c4 12. a3 c5 13. Ke2 Bb7 14. Nd2
$16) 11... c4 12. Bxa7) 8. O-O c4 $5 {Black is forcing matters in a hope to
get activity} 9. e5 $1 {The only way White can pretend for an advantage!} Qb6+
(9... Nd7 10. d4 $1 {White blocks the center and switches to a dark-squared
strategy. However, in contrast to the game Tiviakov-Malakhov, here Black can
carry out the c5 break} (10. dxc4 Ba6 11. b3 dxc4 (11... h6 12. a3 {There is
no time to include a3 and react with b4 to Black's c4} dxc4 13. b4) 12. Re1
$132 ({I was intrigued by this sacrifice to keep the light-squared bishop shut
but unfortunately, it does not work} 12. b4 Bxb4)) (10. Kh1 cxd3 11. cxd3 c5)
10... O-O 11. Be3 c5) 10. Kh1 Ng4 {Even though the move appears to be active,
it only leaves the knight strangled on the side of the board} (10... Nd7 11. d4
c5 (11... Bb7 12. Qe1 c5 13. Be3 $16 cxd4 14. Nxd4 Qa6 15. Qg3 {White's attack
develops on its own} (15. f5)) 12. f5 {Black comes under great attack: White's
initiative on the kingside is rather dangerous}) 11. d4 Nh6 12. Na4 Qb5 13. c3
(13. b3 $3 {Now with the knight isolated on h6, White has even more incentive
to focus on the dark squares in the center!} Ba6 14. Re1 Nf5 (14... Ng4 15. Kg1
$1 {h3 chasing the knight is to come} (15. Qd2 $16)) 15. Be3 $1 Nxe3 16. Rxe3
c5 (16... O-O 17. Qe1 {[%cal Ye1g3] White quickly develops initiative on the
kingside}) (16... cxb3 {is a positional blunder} 17. cxb3 {[%csl Rc6][%cal
Ya1c1,Yc1c6,Ye3c3]}) 17. dxc5 (17. f5) 17... Bxc5 18. Nxc5 Qxc5 19. Nd4 Rc8 20.
c3 $18 {The difference in strength between the minor pieces is obvious} O-O 21.
b4 Qb6 22. a4 {White dominates the whole board}) 13... Rb8 14. Qc2 Bd7 15. Be3
Nf5 16. Bf2 h5 17. Rfb1 O-O 18. h3 g6 (18... h4 19. Nc5) 19. Kh2 Kg7 20. g4
hxg4 21. hxg4 Rh8+ 22. Kg2 Nh4+ $6 23. Bxh4 Bxh4 24. Nc5 Bc8 25. b3 (25. g5)
25... Qa5 26. g5 Qa3 27. Rh1 a5 28. Nxh4 Rxh4 29. Rxh4 cxb3 30. Nxb3 a4 31. Qc1
1-0

