1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 e6 4. Nf3 d5 5. Bb5 Nf6 6. Qe2 (6. Bxc6+ $1 {is more
precise}) 6... Be7 7. O-O $2 O-O $2 ({Black could have prevented the doubling
of his pawns:} 7... Bd7 $1 8. e5 Ng4 $132 {Black is doing fine}) 8. Bxc6 bxc6
9. d3 {Gives Black a chance to get counterplay with the immediate c4} (9. e5 $1
Nd7 10. d3 Ba6 11. Re1 c4 {Black's only chance of improving his position} (
11... d4 $2 {A big positional mistake- Black surrenders the control over the
center and gets a static pawn structure} 12. Ne4 Nb6 13. b3 $3 {Stopping the
c5-c4 advance! White is not afraid of the Nd5 as it is unsupported: the rest
of Black's army is very passive} Nd5 14. Bd2 $18 {The light-squared position
has no hope of ever coming into the game. It is only a matter of time for
White to convert his advantage.} Bb7 15. g4 Qc7 (15... Nc7 16. h4 c4 {A
desperate attempt to open up the bishop. However, Black is simply a pawn down}
17. bxc4 c5) (15... a5 16. a4 {Once and for all stopping Black's play} (16. f5
{is counting on the kingside attack to decide the game})) 16. g5 {Prevents
Black's f6- break; Next, White will start pushing the h-pawn} (16. f5)) 12. d4
c5 13. Be3 Rb8 14. Rab1 {White's plan is to start a kingside attack after g4,
f5}) 9... a5 (9... c4 $1 $132 10. dxc4 (10. d4 Nxe4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Qxe4 Qd5
$36) (10. e5 {Too late} cxd3 (10... Nd7 11. d4) 11. cxd3 Nd7 {Black is doing
great: he has fixed his structure and found a target for his light-squared
bishop} 12. d4 c5 {[%cal Ya7a5,Yc8a6]} (12... a5)) 10... Ba6 11. b3 $2 dxc4 12.
b4 Bxb4 $17) 10. b3 Ba6 11. e5 $1 Nd7 12. Na4 (12. Qf2 $1 c4 13. dxc4 dxc4 14.
Rd1 Qc7 15. Be3 $16) 12... Bb5 $2 (12... c4 $1 $132) (12... Qc7 $2 13. c4 $16)
13. Nb2 a4 14. c4 {fails tactically} (14. Be3 $1 $14) 14... a3 $2 (14... axb3
$3 15. cxb5 Rxa2 16. Be3 cxb5 $17) 15. Nd1 $16 {White is much better again} Ba6
16. Nc3 Bc8 17. Bd2 Nb8 18. Na4 f6 19. Rad1 Nd7 20. exf6 Rxf6 21. Bc3 d4 22.
Bd2 Bd6 23. Ng5 Rh6 24. Ne4 Qe7 25. g3 Rg6 26. Rde1 Nf6 27. Nxd6 Qxd6 28. Nb6
Rb8 29. Nxc8 Rxc8 30. Qxe6+ Qxe6 31. Rxe6 Nd7 32. Re7 Rc7 33. Re8+ Kf7 34. Rfe1
h5 35. f5 Rg4 36. Bf4 Nf6 37. Ra8 Rxf4 38. gxf4 1-0

