{White has a very deep idea here that helps him achieve his long-term plan of
attacking c5. Currently, there are issues reaching the pawn as Nc3 (intending
Na4) runs into dxc4 and Rd2; on the other hand, if White does not play Nc3
right away, Black will push d4 and stop it once and for all. How should White
play?} 2. Re1 $3 {A fantastic move! White prepares to react with Re2 after
possible dxc4 and Rd2. Additionally, he stops d4 as the e6 pawn is hanging
after exd4!} Kf7 (2... d4 3. exd4 cxd4 4. Rxe6+) 3. Nc3 $3 d4 {White does not
take on d4- the c5 pawn needs to stay on the board!} (3... dxc4 4. dxc4 Rd2+ 5.
Re2 Rxe2+ 6. Kxe2 Be7 7. Na4 {Black's c5 pawn is a goner}) 4. Ne4 $3 {Better
than Na4} (4. Na4 {gives Black the hidden resource of...} Bb5 $3 $14 5. cxb5
cxb5 {[%csl Ra4]}) 4... Be7 5. Ba3 $16 *

