{Is White's advantage sufficient for a win?} 10. g4 $1 {A very important move!
White stops all Black's counterplay with f5, g4, Bh6!} (10. Ba3 $2 g4+) 10...
Be7 11. Ba3 $1 {White ties the Black forces to protect the pawn. If he does
not do so, Black will regroup with the ugly-looking Bd8-Ba7-Kd6 and keep c5
safe} (11. Nf1 Bd8 12. Ba3 Bb6) 11... Kf7 12. Nf1 Ke8 13. Ng3 Kd7 14. Nh1 Kc7
15. Nf2 Kb6 16. Nd1 Kb7 17. Nb2 Kc7 18. Na4 Kb7 19. h3 $1 $18 {White is not in
a hurry to take the pawn!} Bd6 20. Ke2 *

